data.message:
I just finished the final read through of Ugly Love. I've decided after several months of heart wrenching torture, the next book I write is going to be about rainbows and unicorns and teddy bears and Harry Connick, Jr.

My eyes hurt.

Preposterous. Gander the Service Dog challenging ME to a contest of follicular facial foliage?? Granted he's cute, and Gander & his hero dog friends make a huge difference in people's lives...but to dis the beard? Time to put this precocious pooch in the back yard. Read the link for his challenge, and my retort, below. 
---------
BEARD BATTLE!!!
Oh, yes, I am most definitely in! But let's not pussyfoot around this wager thing, Lonnie -- Gander and I both have beards of divine bestowal...even if they could be shaved (and the beard itself would fight with the strength of ten men), either one of us would grow it right back in a week with no sweat.

Let's put something SERIOUS on the table: our domes!! I'm talking Full Chrome. You and your losing partner were thinking too small (and on the wrong ends of our skulls) both Gander and I are deficient in fur on the top end...so I raise your unmanly bet: instead of our strengths, I dare Gander to lose ALL follicular product in our weakest area--on the TOPS of our skulls!

That's hitting where it hurts. And when I win, I will let you choose the finest groomer on the face of the planet to exact the price of shame and defeat from the top of Gander's head.

In the laughably unlikely event that I should *lose* the Beard Battle (I feel silly even mentioning this--it's like debating the existence of purple unicorns), then I will happily hold my head up low and let the Finest Barber In The World lather me up and scalp me down.

You ready to tuck tail yet??

data.message:
Guess I have to bring up New York Bully Crew again. I keep getting messages, a lot of them rude, about our support for this organization.

Allegations were made yet there was no evidence to support it. I did receive some poorly done screenshots that showed another group made a donation to NYBC then canceled it. Does that mean NYBC did something wrong? No. I got a link to a forum and a website with a timeline of events. Again, no screen captures. I can write a timeline of events about how unicorns had a slumber party at my house, would you believe it?

If you are going to accuse a group of wrong doing, come with some hard evidence and please don't be upset with us because we don't jump on every bandwagon that travels through our town.

P.S. YES, I mistakenly said Chris when I meant Craig (Craig runs NYBC and was more than happy to share his side of the story with us on the phone). A snarky commenter (who was deleted) implied I got the name wrong because we didn't have a long conversation. No, I got the name wrong because I'm human and make mistakes.

Anyway, check out NYBC's adoptables here: http://nybullycrew.org/adoptables-2/ they deserve to be shared with everyone you know because in the end, this is about DOGS, not personal vendettas.

data.message: You guys. How come no one told me I had a unicorn thing?

Brianna is driving me CRAZY!! She keeps trying to do everything I do, and it’s really starting to bug me!

Yesterday morning I caught her wearing my clothes…and by that I mean my new bra, on top of her shirt. Ewwww! Then last night I caught her texting Zoey…on my phone! She actually took it out my room then typed in: “SUP Zoee??”

First of all, who says, “sup”? And secondly, she spelled her name wrong. And don’t even get me started on the HUGELY IMPORTANT sisterhood commandment she broke: Thou shalt not touch Nikki’s electronics!!

My mom keeps telling the both of us that one day we’ll be best friends. You never know…that might happen, just like I MIGHT grow a unicorn horn and gallop across a rainbow. But regardless, it’s not happening now!

Do any of you have siblings who do annoying stuff like this??
Thanks for sharing, Jennifer! I've seen these done up as unicorns, too.
